589
00:42:42,970 --> 00:42:46,210
DON'T DO THAT.

590
00:42:46,210 --> 00:42:48,620
First, sit down. Oh, really.

591
00:42:48,620 --> 00:42:50,210
Aiyoo, sit still.

592
00:42:50,210 --> 00:42:52,170
You're so shy for a man.

593
00:42:52,170 --> 00:42:54,170
Oh, seriously.

594
00:42:54,170 --> 00:42:58,050
Why is your skin so soft?

595
00:42:58,050 --> 00:43:01,210
Oh hey, you're good looking.

596
00:43:13,900 --> 00:43:15,890
It's been a long time.!

597
00:43:19,780 --> 00:43:22,820
Wait, Hyungnims!

598
00:43:31,780 --> 00:43:33,630
Hyungnim.

599
00:43:34,480 --> 00:43:37,650
Why do you keep asking me to dig the ground?

600
00:43:38,690 --> 00:43:41,360
Kimchi-making season is over.
(Kimchi used to be stored underground)

601
00:43:41,390 --> 00:43:43,210
That's enough. Stop.

602
00:43:43,250 --> 00:43:45,900
Ah. Ah, yes.

603
00:43:48,580 --> 00:43:51,870
He's going to sleep. Cover him.

604
00:43:53,700 --> 00:43:55,980
Oh wait. Please.

605
00:43:56,030 --> 00:44:00,010
Hyungnim! Why do you do this, Hyungnim?

606
00:44:05,880 --> 00:44:07,400
You took our money.

607
00:44:07,400 --> 00:44:12,170
Did you think that if you ran away from Vietnam that
we couldn't follow you?

608
00:44:13,960 --> 00:44:15,580
It's the global age.

609
00:44:15,580 --> 00:44:19,500
Our branches are embedded all over the world.

610
00:44:19,500 --> 00:44:21,240
No matter where you go,

611
00:44:21,240 --> 00:44:23,260
you'll get caught.

612
00:44:27,420 --> 00:44:29,550
What should we do?

613
00:44:32,680 --> 00:44:36,950
This is the list of politicians and businessmen who will be in
attendance at the anniversary celebration.

614
00:44:36,950 --> 00:44:40,880
Once the reception is finished, we're planning to go
right into the dinner.

615
00:44:42,350 --> 00:44:46,260
But... there's something I'm curious about.

616
00:44:47,270 --> 00:44:50,510
Why did you change the date of the founding of our company?

617
00:44:50,530 --> 00:44:52,290
It originally wasn't this day.

618
00:44:52,310 --> 00:44:54,850
This day...
- That day was

619
00:44:56,250 --> 00:45:00,160
the day when my Heaven and Hell crossed paths.

620
00:45:52,890 --> 00:45:54,800
Mother.

621
00:45:55,770 --> 00:45:58,210
Dad!

622
00:46:00,570 --> 00:46:02,870
I'm sorry.

623
00:46:04,900 --> 00:46:07,400
Cha Jeong Woo, don't!

624
00:46:07,400 --> 00:46:09,350
Your life is a precious thing!

625
00:46:09,350 --> 00:46:11,550
Cha Jeong Woo, Cha Jeong Woo, don't!

626
00:46:11,550 --> 00:46:13,360
Mr. Cha Jeong Woo! Calm down!

627
00:46:13,360 --> 00:46:15,740
Mr. Cha Jeong, don't!

628
00:46:15,740 --> 00:46:19,300
M-Mr. Cha Jeong, don't.

629
00:46:20,260 --> 00:46:21,820
Mr. Cha-

630
00:46:21,820 --> 00:46:23,840
Oh, of all things.

631
00:46:37,490 --> 00:46:41,310
How could a man not have a strong will?

632
00:46:41,310 --> 00:46:44,900
Is this the tutor that Seung Hyeon requested?

633
00:47:03,970 --> 00:47:06,490
Yeo Jin,

634
00:47:06,490 --> 00:47:09,400
how long has it been?

635
00:47:31,380 --> 00:47:33,670
How much money did you say this boy needed?

636
00:47:33,670 --> 00:47:36,880
If you're going to invest money in exchange
for management rights,

637
00:47:38,810 --> 00:47:41,480
I won't accept it.

638
00:47:41,520 --> 00:47:45,800
A guy who was on the brink of death is now
being nitpicky with the terms, huh?

639
00:47:45,800 --> 00:47:50,160
I had no intention of dying.

640
00:47:54,930 --> 00:47:57,690
It's because I was so completely surprised.

641
00:48:05,400 --> 00:48:09,890
At that time, the company and I were both reborn.

642
00:48:10,810 --> 00:48:13,330
That's why I changed it to this day.

643
00:48:15,270 --> 00:48:18,370
It's also the day we first met.

644
00:48:40,060 --> 00:48:42,270
What is it all of a sudden?

645
00:48:44,610 --> 00:48:47,030
What happened to your face?

646
00:48:48,360 --> 00:48:50,580
Because you don't come home often,

647
00:48:50,630 --> 00:48:53,390
Oppa came to see you.

648
00:48:53,430 --> 00:48:56,670
I don't have time, so just get to the point.

649
00:49:01,040 --> 00:49:03,220
Could it be...

650
00:49:03,220 --> 00:49:07,180
the rent deposit for my studio apartment that
you stole before you left for Vietnam,

651
00:49:07,180 --> 00:49:09,560
did you come here to cough it up?

652
00:49:17,410 --> 00:49:18,630
What is this?

653
00:49:18,630 --> 00:49:20,730
Obviously, it's money.

654
00:49:20,730 --> 00:49:21,930
Really?

655
00:49:21,930 --> 00:49:23,880
Is it really money?

656
00:49:29,630 --> 00:49:31,890
It's $5000.

657
00:49:36,060 --> 00:49:39,790
What is it? Where did you get this?

658
00:49:41,560 --> 00:49:43,760
What is it? Say it quickly.

659
00:49:43,800 --> 00:49:47,410
Brother-in-law gave it to me.

660
00:49:48,470 --> 00:49:50,740
What?
- He said that it was alimony.

661
00:49:50,760 --> 00:49:52,960
He said you left it there.

662
00:50:01,820 --> 00:50:03,580
For real.

663
00:50:03,590 --> 00:50:06,500
I only went because he called me there.

664
00:50:06,500 --> 00:50:08,110
Sis, please trust me.

665
00:50:08,110 --> 00:50:10,180
And so, did you ask for money when you got there?

666
00:50:10,180 --> 00:50:11,610
No!

667
00:50:11,610 --> 00:50:14,360
I swear, if I had asked him for something, I'll be struck by lightning!

668
00:50:14,360 --> 00:50:18,760
When I got there, he put an envelope out as if he had been waiting to.

669
00:50:18,760 --> 00:50:20,960
He said that you wouldn't take it.

670
00:50:20,960 --> 00:50:23,950
After thinking about it, I figured you needed the money,

671
00:50:23,950 --> 00:50:26,070
but it seemed like (you refused) because of your pride.

672
00:50:26,070 --> 00:50:28,510
What good is family for?

673
00:50:28,510 --> 00:50:29,790
To help you out in times like this . . .

674
00:50:29,790 --> 00:50:33,160
Who asked you to do that?!

675
00:50:35,630 --> 00:50:40,680
In any case, I'm just the messenger.

676
00:50:40,680 --> 00:50:42,840
And . . .

677
00:50:42,900 --> 00:50:44,300
And what?

678
00:50:44,300 --> 00:50:47,340
What! What! What more is there?

679
00:50:47,340 --> 00:50:50,200
That's, well, a handling fee.

680
00:50:50,200 --> 00:50:52,520
A handling fee?

681
00:50:52,520 --> 00:50:54,340
I took a slight amount from it.

682
00:50:54,340 --> 00:50:57,430
After all, I did do some work in getting it.

683
00:51:01,480 --> 00:51:03,600
Oppa, tell me clearly.

684
00:51:03,650 --> 00:51:05,590
How much did you get?

685
00:51:13,020 --> 00:51:14,940
Three thousand won ($30,000)?

686
00:51:15,810 --> 00:51:17,160
Three hundred million won ($300,000).

687
00:51:17,160 --> 00:51:19,150
What? Three hundred million?

688
00:51:20,030 --> 00:51:23,990
Wait, so you got $300,000 and put $5000 in here?

689
00:51:27,950 --> 00:51:30,100
Don't say anything more and just give it here.
I'm going to return it to him.

690
00:51:30,100 --> 00:51:31,880
Quit messing around.
-I don't have it.

691
00:51:31,880 --> 00:51:34,570
What do you mean you don't have it?
Where is it? Give it to me now.

692
00:51:34,570 --> 00:51:36,430
No matter how desperate I am,
I can't take that money.

693
00:51:36,430 --> 00:51:38,510
I'll give it back to him,
so hurry up and give it, where is it?

694
00:51:38,510 --> 00:51:41,580
I don't have the money, honestly.

695
00:51:41,580 --> 00:51:43,690
What do you mean, you don't have it?

696
00:51:45,220 --> 00:51:46,470
Ae Ra,

697
00:51:46,470 --> 00:51:48,430
please forgive me just this once.

698
00:51:48,430 --> 00:51:52,220
While I was in Vietnam running my business,
I borrowed a huge amount of money, and...

699
00:51:52,220 --> 00:51:54,720
those guys wanted to kill me!

700
00:51:54,720 --> 00:51:57,080
I'm telling you that I almost died!

701
00:51:57,080 --> 00:52:00,420
My heart was pounding so much!
I just couldn't live like that!

702
00:52:08,300 --> 00:52:10,360
Ae Ra,

703
00:52:10,360 --> 00:52:15,170
since it's already happened,
let's look on the bright side.

704
00:52:15,170 --> 00:52:17,840
To someone like him, this three hundred million won ($300,000)?

705
00:52:17,840 --> 00:52:19,190
It's not even money to him.

706
00:52:19,190 --> 00:52:22,060
Can you really not shut your mouth?

707
00:52:26,180 --> 00:52:29,230
Get lost! Get lost, you!

708
00:52:29,230 --> 00:52:32,470
Just get out of my life!

709
00:52:32,470 --> 00:52:36,560
This is why I don't like the men in our family!

710
00:52:36,560 --> 00:52:39,970
Dad constantly sucks Mom dry,

711
00:52:39,970 --> 00:52:43,710
and Oppa, you always try to take whatever you can from me!

712
00:52:43,710 --> 00:52:46,370
Do you know what kind of money that is?

713
00:52:46,370 --> 00:52:50,150
That punk promised me that he'd
never make me work in my life.

714
00:52:50,150 --> 00:52:53,600
That turned out to be a lie, and he felt sorry for it.

715
00:52:53,600 --> 00:52:56,440
Saying that he was sorry for making
such an empty promise,

716
00:52:56,440 --> 00:53:00,550
he gave that money to make me get lost!
Do you get it?!

717
00:53:00,550 --> 00:53:02,930
Not just that,

718
00:53:02,930 --> 00:53:04,950
he said I'd have to sign an agreement
before he'd give me that money...

719
00:53:04,950 --> 00:53:06,920
He said he'd give me the money only if I signed the agreement!

720
00:53:06,920 --> 00:53:10,600
That's why I didn't take it,
because he was so dirty and petty!

721
00:53:10,600 --> 00:53:14,720
But you took that money! That money!

722
00:53:45,920 --> 00:53:48,580
Should I go up or do you want to come down?

723
00:53:48,580 --> 00:53:51,530
There's a park in front of the office. I'll see you there.

724
00:53:51,530 --> 00:53:53,310
Okay.

725
00:53:57,090 --> 00:54:00,400
D&T Soft Ventures. 3 year Establishment Anniversary.

726
00:54:00,400 --> 00:54:03,170
Friday February 14, 2014. Golden Tree Hotel Garden Square.

727
00:54:18,810 --> 00:54:20,330
I don't have time.

728
00:54:20,330 --> 00:54:22,270
What is it you wanted to say.

729
00:54:23,160 --> 00:54:24,830
I won't talk long.

730
00:54:24,860 --> 00:54:28,330
You gave money to my brother.

731
00:54:28,330 --> 00:54:29,650
So it was that after all.

732
00:54:29,650 --> 00:54:31,630
I told you that I wouldn't accept it.

733
00:54:31,630 --> 00:54:35,380
Why did you uselessly give it to my brother and
make a person the fool?

734
00:54:35,380 --> 00:54:37,960
Protecting your pride once is enough.

735
00:54:37,960 --> 00:54:41,380
I thought that you had sent him, because you were embarrassed to accept it yourself.

736
00:54:45,770 --> 00:54:47,500
Fine.

737
00:54:48,940 --> 00:54:52,170
Whether I took it, or my Oppa took it...

738
00:54:52,170 --> 00:54:54,870
anyway, okay, I accepted it.

739
00:54:54,870 --> 00:54:59,140
I didn't want to take it and let your mind be comfortable,
so I wasn't going to accept it,

740
00:54:59,140 --> 00:55:01,070
but I took it.

741
00:55:01,070 --> 00:55:04,960
When I think about it, there's no reason not to take it.

742
00:55:06,960 --> 00:55:09,580
I'll graciously accept it and spend it well.

743
00:55:10,360 --> 00:55:15,270
With this everything between us truly ends.

744
00:55:15,270 --> 00:55:17,630
There won't be any reason to see you again, so

745
00:55:17,630 --> 00:55:22,320
you live your life, and I'll live my life. Alright?

746
00:55:22,320 --> 00:55:24,130
I came here to say this to you:

747
00:55:24,130 --> 00:55:26,860
Eat well and live well.

748
00:55:36,830 --> 00:55:39,170
Hey, Cha Jeong Woo!

749
00:55:41,990 --> 00:55:44,080
Let me ask you one last thing.

750
00:55:44,080 --> 00:55:47,800
Is the anniversary of your company's
establishment really February 14?

751
00:55:52,330 --> 00:55:56,570
That date from three years ago is the day we divorced.

752
00:55:56,590 --> 00:55:59,870
Did you really set up this company on that date?

753
00:56:01,170 --> 00:56:04,000
Ah, so you didn't know.

754
00:56:04,050 --> 00:56:08,310
As soon as I divorced you, that very day a
large investment came in.

755
00:56:08,350 --> 00:56:09,780
What?

756
00:56:09,800 --> 00:56:11,970
Isn't it amazing?

757
00:56:11,970 --> 00:56:14,820
As soon as you got out of my life,

758
00:56:14,820 --> 00:56:17,110
things started working out.

759
00:56:19,770 --> 00:56:24,330
Even then, you didn't contact me all this time?

760
00:56:25,060 --> 00:56:27,540
Why should I have called you?

761
00:56:29,140 --> 00:56:30,930
Do you have no loyalty?

762
00:56:30,930 --> 00:56:32,540
Loyalty?

763
00:56:33,940 --> 00:56:36,960
All I did was to carry out your request.

764
00:56:36,980 --> 00:56:38,720
What?

765
00:56:47,330 --> 00:56:49,350
Don't you remember?

766
00:56:52,040 --> 00:56:54,320
Valentine's day.

767
00:56:54,350 --> 00:56:56,340
The day we broke up.

768
00:57:00,100 --> 00:57:03,400
"Don't use alimony as an excuse to call me."

769
00:57:04,260 --> 00:57:07,760
"Just quietly get out of my life."

770
00:57:07,800 --> 00:57:11,090
Don't use alimony as an excuse to call me.

771
00:57:11,090 --> 00:57:13,240
Just quietly,

772
00:57:14,020 --> 00:57:17,100
get out of my life.

773
00:57:17,100 --> 00:57:19,040
I'll make that request

774
00:57:19,040 --> 00:57:21,160
this time.

775
00:57:27,390 --> 00:57:30,530
Quietly get out of my life,

776
00:57:32,450 --> 00:57:34,130
Na Ae Ra.

777
00:57:40,680 --> 00:57:44,080
Even if you had come back because of the money,

778
00:57:44,080 --> 00:57:46,650
